<html>
 <head>
  <link rel="stylesheet"
 href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css"
 crossorigin="anonymous">
 <style>
.button {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 15px 25px;
  font-size: 10px;
  cursor: pointer;
  text-align: center;
  text-decoration: none;
  outline: none;
  color: #fff;
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 15px;
  box-shadow: 0 9px #999;
}

.button:hover {background-color: #3e8e41}

.button:active {
  background-color: #257fd9;
  box-shadow: 0 5px #666;
  transform: translateY(4px);
}
</style>
 <script>
    function toggleConcepts() {
    var x = document.getElementById("mtls-concept-flows");
    if (x.style.display === "none") {
        x.style.display = "block";
    } else {
        x.style.display = "none";
    }
}
</script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container" style="padding:20px">
        <div class="card card-body bg-light">
        
        <h3>
            <a href="/home">
                <img src="images/logo.png" alt="Cloudentity logo"  width="42" height="42" />
            </a>
            Cloudentity OAuth MTLS Bound Tokens & Enforcement 
        </h3>
        <div>
            <p>
                <button onclick="toggleConcepts()" class="button">Let's talk about some concepts</button>
            </p>
            <div id="mtls-concept-flows" style="display:none">
                <div>
                    <p> Some keywords that would be of interest to the audience as we step into this demo, 
                    for mTLS OAuth RFC and Cloudentity implementation support </p>
                    <img src="images/rfc-8705-keywords.jpeg" alt="Cloudentity logo" style="height: 100%; width: 100%; object-fit: contain" />
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4> Using OAuth mTLS flows in Application architectures </h4>
                    <p> Let's dive into how will these flows augment secure application development practices and architectures </p>
                    <img src="images/mtls-concept.jpeg" alt="Cloudentity logo"  style="height: 100%; width: 100%; object-fit: contain" />
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4> Demo setup - let's prove it out! </h4>
                    <p> Let's make sure this is just not some pretty boxes and we have some demo apps to back the concepts. </p>
                    <img src="images/mtls-demo-setup.jpeg" alt="Cloudentity logo" style="height: 100%; width: 100%; object-fit: contain" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <a href="/auth">Get Access Token</a>
            <pre  id="regular_access_token"> {{{accessToken}}} </pre>
        </div>
        <div>
            <a href="/mtlsauth">Get Certificate Bound Access Token</a>
            <pre id="certificate_bound_access_token"> {{{certificate_bound_access_token}}} </pre>
        </div>
        <div>
            <a href="/mtls-resource">Call Resource server with Certificate Bound Access Token</a>
            <pre id="mtls_resource"> {{mtls_resource}} </pre>
        </div>
        <div>
            <a href="/mtls-resource-roguecaller">Call Resource server with different TLS client certificate</a>
            <pre id="mtls_resource"> {{mtls_resource_rogue_caller}} </pre>
        </div>
        
    </div>
  </div>
 </body>
</html>